{{short description|Book by Herta Müller}} {{italic title}} '''{{lang|de|In der Falle: Drei Essays}}''' ({{Literal translation|In the Trap: Three Essays}}) is a book by [[Nobel Prize in Literature|Nobel Prize]]-winning author [[Herta Müller]].<ref name="Chiellino 2000">{{cite book | last = Chiellino | first = C. | title = Interkulturelle Literatur in Deutschland.: Ein Handbuch. | publisher = Metzlersche J.B. Verlagsb | year = 2000 | isbn = 978-3-476-01618-8 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=6KtiAAAAMAAJ | language = de | access-date = 25 July 2018 | page = 484 }}</ref> It was first published in 1996 by {{ill|Wallstein Verlag|de}}.<ref name="Spiridon 2002">{{cite book | last = Spiridon | first = O. | title = Untersuchungen zur rumäniendeutschen Erzählliteratur der Nachkriegszeit | publisher = Igel | series = Reihe Literatur- und Medienwissenschaft | year = 2002 | isbn = 978-3-89621-150-7 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=ZeNbAAAAMAAJ | language = de | access-date = 25 July 2018 | page = 338 }}</ref> The book consists of essays about the autobiographical poetry of three writers, [[Theodor Kramer]], [[Ruth Klüger]] and [[Inge Müller]], who wrote under conditions of dictatorship.<ref>{{cite book | last = Symons | first = Morwenna | authorlink = | title = Room for Maneuver | publisher = [[Modern Humanities Research Association]] | series = | volume = | edition = | date = 2005 | location = | pages = | language = | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=j8UoVW25g_kC&pg=PA106&lpg=PA106&dq=in+der+falle+herta+müller&source=bl&ots=CqNE6kYPH2&sig=gUyNfVWQYzNq9Ep6sfFgUXX_xas&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiUlIeTpLPcAhX4IjQIHS8fB-w4ChDoATAOegQIARAB#v=onepage&q=in%20der%20falle%20herta%20müller&f=false | doi = | id = | isbn = 978-1-904350-43-9 | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last = Seeling | first = Mathias | authorlink = | title = Überleben und Schreiben: Herta Müller: 'In der Falle' und das Moment der Todesangst in der Literatur eines diktatorischen Reg