'''Kipu Falls''' is a [[waterfall]] in East Kauai, [[Hawaii]].

Kipu Falls has a dangerous reputation due to [[drowning]] deaths of five people in a five-year span, as well as numerous other injuries. Due to the drowning deaths, Grove Farms Company, which owns the land where the falls are located, decided to block off the access route. From a legal perspective, visitors were [[trespassing]], as the falls were not actually open to the public. Injuries became more prevalent after guide books began publicizing the falls.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/19/kipu-falls-hawaii-swimming-hole_n_903502.html | title=Kipu Falls, Hawaii Swimming Hole, Is A Deadly Tourist Trap | date=September 18, 2011 | publisher=Associated Press | accessdate=2017-07-11}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.hawaiinewsnow.com/story/15328936/owner-of-deadly-kauai-swimming-hole-blocks-access | title=Kauai's popular Kipu Falls fenced-off | publisher=Hawaii News Now | year=2011 | first=Brooks | last=Baehr | accessdate=2017-07-11}}</ref>

Kipu Falls is also widely known for being the filming location of the introduction scene of ''[[Raiders of the Lost Ark]]''.

