{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Lowell Regio |image = Lowell Regio on Pluto.jpg |caption = |type = Region |location = [[Pluto]] |latitude = |N_or_S = |longitude = |E_or_W = |globe = |coordinates_footnotes = <ref>citation</ref> |length = |width = |diameter = |depth = |area = |dimensions = |peak = |discoverer = ''[[New Horizons]]'' |naming = [[Percival Lowell]] |eponym = }} [[File:Lowell Regio.jpg|thumb|Lowell Regio]] '''Lowell Regio''' ({{IPAc-en|ˈ|l|oʊ|əl|,_|ˈ|l|oʊ|l}}) is a region on the [[dwarf planet]] [[Pluto]]. It was discovered by the ''[[New Horizons]]'' spacecraft in 2015. The region corresponds to the Plutonian northern polar cap. It is named after [[Percival Lowell]] who established the observatory where [[Clyde Tombaugh]] discovered Pluto.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Beal|first1=Tom|title=Tombaugh, Lowell honored|url=http://tucson.com/tombaugh-lowell-honored/article_c6ae2d1e-411c-11e5-9cf5-7347e420cecb.html|accessdate=11 September 2015|work=[[Arizona Daily Star]]|date=August 12, 2015}}</ref>
